            "answer_text": "There are multiple treatments for the plague. The earliest, a vaccine, was developed by Waldemar Haffkine at the end of the 19th century. Haffkine was a busy guy, who also developed a vaccine for cholera. Since then, there have been several other regimens developed for treatment of the plague. It turns out to be vulnerable to a variety of antibiotics. It needs to be caught early, but once treatments were first discovered, it turned out to be very easy to cure. ",
